<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-50-0051 </DOCNO><TEXT>A case of a bilateral isolated internal iliac aneurysm is presented. Amale patient of 74 years of age had a sudden attack of pain in the rightlower abdomen. A superficial haematoma was the only finding at primaryultrasonography (US), while seven weeks later a control US visualiseda pelvic expansion, but the aetiology was not recognised. The CT findingwas pathognomonic for an aneurysm, the diagnosis being 'bilateral iliacaneurysms'. Digital subtraction angiography (DSA) defined the aneurysmsas existing in the internal iliac arteries.</TEXT></DOC>